==English==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|es|sombrero|t=hat}}, from {{m|es|sombra|t=shadow, shade}} + {{m|es|-ero}}, literally, "shade-maker". The drink was named after the hat.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[File:Sombrero (PSF).png|thumb|sombrero]]

# A kind of [[hat]] with a high conical or cylindrical crown and a saucer-shaped brim, highly embroidered, made of plush felt.
# A mixed drink with [[coffee liqueur]] and [[cream]].
# {{lb|en|bowling}} A series of four consecutive [[strike|strikes]].

